      Things happen
   =20
 =20
Activist Investor Pushes  Peloton to Fire CEO and Seek Sale. Private equity=
 sidesteps IPO parade by=C2=A0borrowing billions. Empty Private Jet Flights=
 Hastened Credit Suisse Chairman=C2=A0Ant=C3=B3nio Horta-Os=C3=B3rio=E2=80=
=99s=C2=A0Downfall. Peltz=E2=80=99s Activist Fund=C2=A0Trian=C2=A0Is Said t=
o Build Stake in Unilever. Shell=E2=80=99s Massive=C2=A0Carbon Capture Plan=
t=C2=A0Is Emitting More Than It=E2=80=99s Capturing.  Algae Market Potentia=
lly Worth $320 Billion Draws Honda, Eneos.=C2=A0Crypto giant Binance kept w=
eak money-laundering checks even as it promised tougher compliance, documen=
ts show. The Charismatic Developer and the  Ponzi Scheme That Suckered San =
Diego.=C2=A0Don't Approach=C2=A0Lab Monkey Missing After Crash, People Told=
.=C2=A0Robot vacuum cleaner=C2=A0escapes=C2=A0from Cambridge Travelodge. Ev=
elyn Davis=E2=80=99s=C2=A0tombstone.If you'd like to get=C2=A0Money=C2=A0St=
uff=C2=A0in handy email form, right in your inbox, please=C2=A0subscribe at=
 this link. Or you can subscribe to Money Stuff and other great Bloomberg n=
ewsletters=C2=A0here. Thanks![1] Those numbers come from page 30 of the mos=
t recent=C2=A0Form 10-Q. MicroStrategy reported=C2=A0a GAAP loss from opera=
tions of $647 million for the nine months ended Sept. 30, 2021, and a non-G=
AAP income from operations, stripping out digital asset impairment=C2=A0 ($=
684=C2=A0million) and share-based compensation ($31 million), of about $68 =
million. I have added back share-based compensation, which I attribute to M=
icroStrategy=E2=80=99s business, to get the $37 million non-GAAP earnings a=
ttributable to the business.[2] You know who else runs an operating busines=
s stapled to a pot of investment assets? Warren Buffett, who also complains=
 that smooshing these things together for GAAP accounting is misleading. At=
 least he gets to mark his investments up when they go up. Anyway I  once w=
rote about his complaints: =E2=80=9CLook: There is a sense in which if you =
run a giant investment fund and you buy stocks and those stocks go down, th=
en you have lost money. I mean there is also a sense in which you haven=E2=
=80=99t, but it is the less conventional sense. I am not going to argue for=
 the objective reality of GAAP net income accounting, and I see Buffett=E2=
=80=99s point that combining a bunch of operating businesses with a hedge f=
und leads to weird accounting results, but on the other hand (1) he=E2=80=
=99s the one who combined them!, and (2) it does feel a little like special=
 pleading for Buffett, a long-time critic of companies that use non-GAAP ac=
counting metrics, to complain that it=E2=80=99s unfair for GAAP to make him=
 report a loss just because the stocks he bought went down.=E2=80=9D
