cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">a Wall Street Journal article</a>=
 about WallStreetBets, the Reddit forum that ignited the GameStop boom and =
became the center of the meme-stock world for a while:</p><blockquote><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">These days, some one-time fans say it is hardly wor=
th clicking on.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those who once scoured the =
online message forum for brazen and unexpected trading ideas say they are m=
ostly finding members still chatting about stocks such as GameStop Corp. an=
d AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc.=C2=A0 Constructive feedback on trades, so=
me users complain, has largely been replaced by cheerleading. Devotees who =
were once glued to the forum=E2=80=94watching power users like Keith Gill, =
or =E2=80=9CDeepF=E2=80=94ingValue,=E2=80=9D post bold bets on GameStop=E2=
=80=94say they have largely abandoned the page in favor of other trading co=
mmunities.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And in this morning=
=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9C5 Things to Start Your Day=E2=80=9D Bloomberg newslette=
r, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26470748.263630=
/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9UaGVTdGFsd2FydC9zdGF0dXMvMTQ4NTU4NTE1NTA3NTAyMj=
g1NA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB33bb12b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Joe Weisenthal writes</a> t=
hat a lot of the memeiest and most retail-driven parts of the market have a=
ctually been underperforming since last February,=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cthe retail =
crowd has been badly lagging the S&amp;P 500 for a while now,=E2=80=9D and =
=E2=80=9Cthe whole =E2=80=98Reddit vs. Hedge Funds=E2=80=99 meme that came =
out of the GameStop story really did turn out to be the peak of the mania.=
=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile the broad stock market =
got crushed all last week and is down more today. The S&amp;P 500 index is =
now in what people like to call a =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/26470748.263630/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2=
xlcy9nbG9iYWwtc3RvY2tzLW1hcmtldHMtZG93LXVwZGF0ZS0wMS0yNC0yMDIyLTExNjQzMDExM=
zIz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe18e6122" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">correction</a>,=E2=80=9D=C2=
=A0a drop of 10% from the most recent high, which in this case is Jan. 3. I=
 have always thought this was sort of=C2=A0a dumb euphemism but now, I mean=
, I guess I see the point.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Long before Game=
Stop, in April 2020, I coined what I have called <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26470748.263630/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDQtMzAvaWYteW91LXJlLWJvcmVkLXlvdS1jYW4=
tdHJhZGUtc3RvY2tzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMjQyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haW=
wmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDEyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZ=
XlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB40dbf6bc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the Boredom Market Hy=
pothesis</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The theory is som=
ething like: Retail investors are not trading=C2=A0because they have an inf=
ormational advantage and a reasonable expectation of profit.=C2=A0They are =
trading because it is fun, or because it looks fun. They see people making =
money in the stock market, it looks fun and easy to make money in the stock=
 market, they start trading stocks. As long as it is fun=E2=80=94as long as=
 stocks go up=E2=80=94they increase their investments. When it stops being =
fun=E2=80=94when stocks go down=E2=80=94they get out.</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">The weird thing about the coronavirus crisis is that it simultan=
eously (1) caused a stock market crash and (2) eliminated most=C2=A0forms o=
f fun.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When the world shut dow=
n in the spring of 2020, people turned to day-trading stocks because, even =
though the market=C2=A0had just crashed, trading stocks was still more fun =
than their other entertainment options. And then trading stocks became, imp=
robably, really fun, a source of social connection and populist excitement,=
 and also those stocks went up a lot which was fun. In 2022, there are more=
 fun things to do, and frantic day trading is less fun than it used=C2=A0to=
 be. It has gotten old; the message boards are not alive with excitement bu=
t are just playing the hits. Also the market is crashing again! Where is th=
e fun in that?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile at noon today Game=
Stop was trading above $88 per share. When I first wrote about GameStop, wh=
en everything went utterly insane, when GameStop=E2=80=99s soaring price se=
emed to make no sense at all, it closed at $76.79. Perhaps we=E2=80=99ll te=
st that today. Or perhaps GameStop used its meme status to successfully <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26470748.263630/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDYtMTAvbWF5YmUt=
Z2FtZXN0b3AtaXMtZ29vZC1ub3c_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEyNDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl=
1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMTI0JnV0bV9jYW1wYW=
lnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8fec1a9e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> transform it=
s business</a>; perhaps=C2=A0the magic doesn=E2=80=99t work anymore, but it=
s effects on GameStop have lasted.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-=
